@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 40px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
      color: #2c3e50;
    }

    h2 {
      color: #34495e;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #eee;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    p {
      margin: 15px 0;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 15px 0;
      padding-left: 30px;
    }

    .last-updated {
      text-align: center;
      color: #7f8c8d;
      font-style: italic;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 50px;
      text-align: center;
      color: #95a5a6;
      font-size: 0.9em;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="last-updated">Last updated: December 19, 2025</p>

  <p>Thank you for visiting our website. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our site.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>This is a <strong>static personal/educational website</strong> (showcasing a React Native project - TP7 Hooks by Pr. Mostafa SAADI).</p>
  <p><strong>We do not collect any personal information</strong> from visitors.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>No forms are present to collect names, emails, or any contact details.</li>
    <li>No user accounts or login system exists.</li>
    <li>No comments, subscriptions, or newsletters are offered.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Data Automatically Collected</h2>
  <p>Like most websites, our web server may automatically log standard information for operational purposes only, such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>IP address</li>
    <li>Browser type</li>
    <li>Referring page</li>
    <li>Date and time of visit</li>
    <li>Pages viewed</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This data is used solely for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Monitoring site performance</li>
    <li>Diagnosing technical issues</li>
    <li>Preventing abuse or attacks</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>We do not use this data to track or identify individual users.</strong></p>

  <h2>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
  <p><strong>We do not use cookies, analytics tools (like Google Analytics), tracking pixels, or any third-party advertising services.</strong></p>
  <p>No data is shared with third parties for marketing or advertising purposes.</p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Links</h2>
  <p>Our site may contain links to external websites (e.g., GitHub, LinkedIn, school platform, etc.). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.</p>

  <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>This website is not directed toward children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the limited server log data we collect. However, no website is 100% secure.</p>

  <h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date.</p>

  <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Name:</strong> [Your Full Name]<br>
    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:your-email@example.com">your-email@example.com</a>
  </p>

  <div class="footer">
    <p>Thank you for visiting!</p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
